<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1306,2012]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1386,1412]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name honors the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[898,948,1386,1412]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
specimen, the arachnologist Diana Silva Dávila, in recognition of her efforts in studying the Peruvian spider fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1306,2012]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1466,1492]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Santos, 2007" authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2007" box="[333,568,1467,1492]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dianasilvae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[333,568,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Architis dianasilvae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[575,669,1466,1492]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[575,669,1466,1492]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carico. A" authorityYear="1981" box="[816,955,1467,1492]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cymatilis">
<emphasis box="[816,955,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. cymatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shape of the CD, which are encapsulated in large, sausage-shaped sclerotised cases (
<figureCitation box="[725,824,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="11.[151,269,1557,1581]" captionTargetBox="[255,1361,188,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-222@11.[204,1383,116,1555]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 3A–D. Architis cymatilis Carico. A, male pedipalpus, ventral view; B, male pedipalpus, lateral view; C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097181/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 3D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[838,871,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="18.[151,269,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,553,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-209@18.[144,1443,474,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 8A–F. Architis spp. A–B, A. ikuruwa Carico: A, female epigynum, ventral view; B, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. C–D, A. altamira sp. nov.: C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. E–F, A. dianasilvae sp. nov.: E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Arrows point to the copulatory opening. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">8F</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by a wide transverse keel in the anterior half of the epigynum, covering the copulatory openings (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1136,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="18.[151,269,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,553,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-209@18.[144,1443,474,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 8A–F. Architis spp. A–B, A. ikuruwa Carico: A, female epigynum, ventral view; B, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. C–D, A. altamira sp. nov.: C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. E–F, A. dianasilvae sp. nov.: E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Arrows point to the copulatory opening. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
