<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1306,2012]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Carapace reddish-brown, dark brown medially and marginally. Anterior eye row procurved, lateral eyes strongly projected ventrally and almost twice as large as medians. Posterior eyes of similar size. Clypeus cream-coloured, chelicerae reddish-brown. Eye sizes and arrangement as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carico. A" authorityYear="1981" box="[1039,1177,1787,1812]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cymatilis">
<emphasis box="[1039,1177,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. cymatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Carico, J. E." box="[1237,1385,1786,1812]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="140 - 153" refId="ref25013" refString="Carico, J. E. (1981) The Neotropical spider genera Architis and Staberius (Pisauridae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 170, 140 - 153." type="journal article" year="1981">Carico 1981</bibRefCitation>
; fig. 11). Sternum cream-coloured, with marginal brown spots at the base of coxae. Labium and endites reddishbrown. Pedipalpi and legs reddish-brown. Opisthosoma dark gray dorsally, with darker spots. Venter and sides cream-coloured, with dark spots. Spinnerets reddish-brown. Total length 4.7; carapace 1.8 long, 1.7 wide. Tibia I length 3.2, II 3.4, III 2.5, IV 2.9. Opisthosoma 2.8 long, 1.5 wide. Epigynal MF projected posteriorly over epigastric furrow (
<figureCitation box="[499,590,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="18.[151,269,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[196,1393,553,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-209@18.[144,1443,474,1907]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 8A–F. Architis spp. A–B, A. ikuruwa Carico: A, female epigynum, ventral view; B, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. C–D, A. altamira sp. nov.: C, female epigynum, ventral view; D, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. E–F, A. dianasilvae sp. nov.: E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Arrows point to the copulatory opening. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097197/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
